{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7bb724b9-cab8-48f5-8706-78995e5b140c","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n`--filter` stays **before** `--`; platform-specific options go **after** it.\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test projects):\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"47dd1874-fc90-471e-94b7-cfd8b73df5f5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `--filter` → `--filter`(same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect code-coverage` (with Microsoft.CodeCoverage package) or use `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` with `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you can still use `dotnet test` and the arguments get forwarded through, though the specific option names have changed to align with the new testing infrastructure.\n\nWhen using `dotnet test`, platform-specific options go after `--`, while filters stay before it. If you run the test executable directly, all options including filters go on the same command line. For code coverage, you'd add the CodeCoverage extension and pass the appropriate coverage format flags.","outputTokens":975},"id":"02ea5a48-981f-465e-a531-faa122b9868c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T13:06:08.262Z","parentId":"0b209521-8865-4fd8-a03c-9f2a22727d4c"}
